With this implementation, the kernel-to-device mapping is tranparently managed by
the local resource manager, as mentioned above. This means that the platform and
device selection calls (lines 7-15) do not have any real effect on the kernel compilation
andoffloading, untilthefunctionclStartComputationiscalled. Heretheprogramming
library waits for the resource manager to provide all the mapping information, before
launching the actual kernel execution. The remaining part of the application (host-side)
code is perfectly OpenCL standard compliant.
